description:
Partial CBCL scale:
(1)	how often would you say that your child has been unable to stay put, or has been restless or hyperactive?
(2)	how often would you say that your child was easily distracted, or had difficulty pursuing any activity?
(3)	how often would you say your child has constantly fidgeted?
(4)	how often would you say that your child has been unable to concentrate, or maintain attention for a long period?
(5)	how often would you say that your child has had difficulty waiting for their turn in a game?
(6)	how often would you say your child has been inattentive/distracted?

Partial CBCL scale: (1) how often would you say that your child has been unable to stay put, or has been restless or hyperactive?
(2) how often would you say that your child has been rebellious or refused to obey?
(3) how often would you say your child has been in a fight?
(4) how often would you say that your child was easily distracted, or had difficulty pursuing any activity?
(5) how often would you say that your child did not seem to feel remorse after misbehaving?
(6) how often would you say your child has constantly fidgeted?
(7) how often would you say that your child has been unable to concentrate, or maintain attention for a long period?
(8) how often would you say that your child has not changed their behaviour after being punished?
(9) how often would you say that your child has had difficulty waiting for their turn in a game?
(10)  how often would you say your child has physically attacked others?
(11)  how often would you say that your child has hit, bitten or kicked other children?
(12)  how often would you say your child has been inattentive/distracted?

description: The variable is partially harmonised because categories were created by categorising household incomes into quartiles, not based on the national household income distribution in the year of follow-up
syntax:
# household income at 31yr
sour["hhincome_own31"] <- NA
sour$hhincome_own31[sour$ZP05 >= quantile(sour$ZP05, na.rm = T)[4]] <- 1
sour$hhincome_own31[sour$ZP05 < quantile(sour$ZP05, na.rm = T)[4] &
                      sour$ZP05 >= quantile(sour$ZP05, na.rm = T)[3]] <- 2
sour$hhincome_own31[sour$ZP05 < quantile(sour$ZP05, na.rm = T)[3] &
                      sour$ZP05 >= quantile(sour$ZP05, na.rm = T)[2]] <- 3
sour$hhincome_own31[sour$ZP05 < quantile(sour$ZP05, na.rm = T)[2]]  <- 4

# make the add_new function
add_new <- function(sour_data, sour_var, new_var, age, method) {
  add <- sour_data[, c("project_ID", sour_var)]
  add["variable"] <- new_var
  add["measure"] <- add[,sour_var]
  if(is.na(age)) {
    add["age"] <- NA
  } else if(is.numeric(age)) {
    add["age"] <- age
  } else {
    add["age"] <- sour_data[,age]
  }
  if(is.na(method)) {
    add["method"] <- NA
  } else {
    add["method"] <- sour_data[,method]
  }
  add <- add[,c("project_ID", "variable", "measure", "age", "method")]
  names(add) <- c("id", "variable", "measure", "age", "method")
  add <- add[!is.na(add$measure),]
}

add <- add_new(sour, "hhincome_own31", "hhincome_own", "age31", NA)
harm <- rbind(harm, add)

# household income at 46yr
sour$C6646Q2_41[sour$C6646Q2_41 == "."] <- NA
sour$C6646Q2_41[sour$C6646Q2_41 == ""] <- NA
sour$C6646Q2_41 <- as.numeric(sour$C6646Q2_41)
sour["hhincome_own46"] <- NA
sour$hhincome_own46[sour$C6646Q2_41 >= quantile(sour$C6646Q2_41, na.rm = T)[4]] <- 1
sour$hhincome_own46[sour$C6646Q2_41 < quantile(sour$C6646Q2_41, na.rm = T)[4] &
                      sour$C6646Q2_41 >= quantile(sour$C6646Q2_41, na.rm = T)[3]] <- 2
sour$hhincome_own46[sour$C6646Q2_41 < quantile(sour$C6646Q2_41, na.rm = T)[3] &
                      sour$C6646Q2_41 >= quantile(sour$C6646Q2_41, na.rm = T)[2]] <- 3

description: 1) gestational hypertension  (BP 145/95 mmHg or more after 20th gestational week. Normal BP in the early pregnancy i.e. (<20th gestational week). Proteinuria at least in one sample during pregnancy). 3) Chronic hypertension a. BP elevated already in early pregnancy ((<20th gestational week), 145/95 mmHg or more, and BP elevated also during whole pregnancy or after pregnancy (6weeks after pregnancy)) b. Chronic hypertension (hypertension essentialis) diagnose registered in questionnaire) 4.) Superimposed pre-eclampsia (chronic hypertension+protenuria, 5) Could not be determinated (all BP values not available 6) not known, 7) Systolic BP elevated Systolic BP >145 and diastolic BP < 95. Includes also women with proteinuria. 8.) Normotensive- BP under 145/95 and is not included in any of the above mentioned groups.9.) DiastolicBP elevated (Diastolic BP >95 and systolic BP < 145, Includes also women with proteinuria).   In the 1960's , BP was recorded by rounding up or down to the nearest 5mmHg, thus values >=145/95 represent hypertension.

syntax:
# occupational status 1982-2011 asked in the 46yr questionnaire
which(colnames(sour)=="C6646Q2_5_82_1") # 84
which(colnames(sour)=="C6646Q2_5_11_7") # 293
varnames <- names(sour[,84:293])
varnames <- substr(varnames,1,12)
varnames <- unique(varnames)

for(i in varnames) {
  year <- gsub("C6646Q2_5_", "", i)
  year <- 1900 + as.numeric(year)
  if (year < 1982) {
    year <- gsub("C6646Q2_5_", "", i)
    year <- gsub("_.*", "", year)
    year <- 2000 + as.numeric(year)
  } 
  var_name <- paste0("occup", year-1966)
  sour[var_name] <- NA
  orig_var1 <- paste0(i,"_",1)
  sour[var_name][sour[paste0(i,"_",7)] == 7] <- 6
  sour[var_name][sour[paste0(i,"_",6)] == 6] <- 5
  sour[var_name][sour[paste0(i,"_",1)] == 1] <- 4
  sour[var_name][sour[paste0(i,"_",5)] == 5] <- 3
  sour[var_name][sour[paste0(i,"_",4)] == 4] <- 2
  sour[var_name][sour[paste0(i,"_",2)] == 2] <- 1
  sour[var_name][sour[paste0(i,"_",3)] == 3] <- 1
}

# occupational status in 31yr questioinnaire
sour$occup31[sour$ZP15 == 1 | sour$ZP15 == 2 | sour$ZP15 == 3] <- 1
sour$occup31[sour$ZP15 == 4 | sour$ZP15 == 5] <- 2
sour$occup31[sour$ZP15 == 7 | sour$ZP15 == 9 | sour$ZP15 == 12] <- 3
sour$occup31[sour$ZP15 == 6 | sour$ZP15 == 8] <- 4
sour$occup31[sour$ZP15 == 10] <- 5
sour$occup31[sour$ZP15 == 11] <- 6

# occupational status in 46yr questioinnaire
sour["occup46"] <- NA
sour$occup46[sour$C6646Q2_1_15 == 15] <- 6
sour$occup46[sour$C6646Q2_1_14 == 14 | sour$C6646Q2_1_16 == 16] <- 5
sour$occup46[sour$C6646Q2_1_7 == 7 | sour$C6646Q2_1_8 == 8 | sour$C6646Q2_1_12 == 12] <- 4
sour$occup46[sour$C6646Q2_1_9 == 9 | sour$C6646Q2_1_10 == 10 | sour$C6646Q2_1_11 == 11 | sour$C6646Q2_1_13 == 13] <- 3
sour$occup46[sour$C6646Q2_1_5 == 5 | sour$C6646Q2_1_6 == 6] <- 2
sour$occup46[sour$C6646Q2_1_1 == 1 | sour$C6646Q2_1_2 == 2 | sour$C6646Q2_1_3 == 3 | sour$C6646Q2_1_4 == 4] <- 1

# make the add_new function
add_new <- function(sour_data, sour_var, new_var, age, method) {
  add <- sour_data[, c("project_ID", sour_var)]
  add["variable"] <- new_var
  add["measure"] <- add[,sour_var]
  if(is.na(age)) {
    add["age"] <- NA
  } else if(is.numeric(age)) {
    add["age"] <- age
  } else {
    add["age"] <- sour_data[,age]
  }
  if(is.na(method)) {
    add["method"] <- NA
  } else {
    add["method"] <- sour_data[,method]
  }
  add <- add[,c("project_ID", "variable", "measure", "age", "method")]
  names(add) <- c("id", "variable", "measure", "age", "method")
  add <- add[!is.na(add$measure),]
}

# add new variables to harmonised variables table
